Here is a tutorial on how you can activate the pack via Scaler:

Step 1: Create a new Github account if you don't have one already. You
can create this account using your Scaler registered email ID. (To
know how to create account, read here:
https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/signing-up-for-github/signing-up-for-a-new-github-account)

Step 2: If you have already have an account using another email ID,
you can add your Scaler registered email to the account (To know how
to add email ID, read here:
https://docs.github.com/en/account-and-profile/setting-up-and-managing-your-personal-account-on-github/managing-email-preferences/adding-an-email-address-to-your-github-account).

Step 3: Verify your email addresses in the Github account (To know how
to verify email address, read here:
https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/signing-up-for-github/verifying-your-email-address).

Step 4: Open the verification link:
https://education.github.com/student/verify?school_id=61444&student_id=contact2theshreya%40gmail.com&signature=4b7f52ccbb028e0dd88f697cd720762f11d0fa400763182ff72615c1714227c7

Step 5: Done! Open https://education.github.com/pack/offers and you
will be able to access all benefits now and explore all the benefits!
Do activate the Jetbrains license from there which will give you
access to IntelliJ and other IDEs. Also, do explore other wonderful
things being offered there.

Thatâ€™s it.

After you have activated Github, you can activate Jetbrains/ IntelliJ
as follows:
1. Open https://www.jetbrains.com/shop/eform/students
2. Click on Github tab
3. Click on Authorize with Github
4. Login using Github, and Done.

Now you can download and install Jetbrains toolbox from
https://www.jetbrains.com/toolbox-app/ and use this to get IntelliJ
Ultimate, etc.
